<td style="padding:0in 0in 0in 0in">
<p class="MsoNormal"><b><span style="color:#4D5357;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB">3 Things in 2 Sentences</span></b><span style="font-size:10.0pt;color:#4D5357;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB"><o:p></o:p></span></p>
<div class="MsoNormal" align="center" style="text-align:center"><span style="font-size:10.0pt;color:#4D5357;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB">
<hr size="1" width="100%" align="center">
</span></div>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:10.0pt;color:#4D5357;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB">Friends,<br>
Here are&nbsp;<s>three</s>&nbsp;four Americas Litigation practice highlights from this week:&nbsp;<o:p></o:p></span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:10.0pt;color:#4D5357;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>
<ol style="margin-top:0in" start="1" type="1">
<li class="MsoListParagraph" style="color:#4D5357;margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:0in;mso-add-space:auto;text-align:left;line-height:normal;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1">
<a name="_Hlk174628318"><span style="font-size:10.0pt;font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif">Late last week, partner Allen Pegg and attorney Robert Leitner (both Miami), supported by partner George Salter (New York) and senior paralegal Gladys Cata (Miami), obtained
 a dismissal on <i>forum</i> <i>non conveniens</i> grounds for a group of defendants (three of whom are embroiled in related litigation in the Netherlands) involved in a U.S. lawsuit, pursued by a team from Sidley Austin alleging that the defendants had, among
 other matters, conspired to interfere with a significant business relationship based at Miami International Airport.&nbsp;Following a nearly two-hour hearing, a judge in the Miami-Dade Circuit Court’s complex business division granted dismissal from the bench,
 having been persuaded by the Hogan Lovells team that the former employees’ Dutch employment agreements’ forum-selection clause warranted dismissal in favor of litigation in the Netherlands, among other arguments.&nbsp;<b>(Transportation)
</b></span></a><span style="font-size:10.0pt;font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif"><o:p></o:p></span></li><li class="MsoNormal" style="color:#4D5357;margin-bottom:12.0pt;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1">
<span style="font-size:10.0pt;background:white">A cross-office team of partners Patrick Michael (San Francisco), Tom Connally and Chris Pickens (both Northern Virginia), senior associates Sam Yergin (Northern Virginia) and Madeleine Bech (San Francisco), and
 associate Kellie Majcher (Northern Virginia) obtained complete dismissal of a complaint filed against our client Synopsys, Inc. by Sunstone Partners Management, LLC in the Delaware Court of Chancery arising out of the potential sale of Synopsys' security testing
 services (STS) business. Sunstone alleged that Synopsys had solicited competing bids in violation of an exclusivity provision in the parties' term sheet by announcing that Synopsys was evaluating &quot;strategic alternatives&quot; for the business unit containing STS,
 and hiring a banker to run that process, but the Court held that these allegations failed to allege any breach by Synopsys, or support any inference of such a breach, even under Delaware's &quot;plaintiff-friendly&quot; pleading standard.&nbsp;<b>(Technology)</b></span><span style="font-size:10.0pt;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB">
<o:p></o:p></span></li><li class="MsoListParagraph" style="color:#4D5357;margin-left:0in;mso-add-space:auto;text-align:left;line-height:normal;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1">
<b><span style="font-size:10.0pt;font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif">CONFIDENTIAL</span></b><span style="font-size:10.0pt;font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif">. For the third week in a row, Disney’s cross-office team of partners Allison Holt Ryan (D.C.), Vassi Iliadis
 (Los Angeles), Mark Cheskin (Miami), counsel Catherine Bratic (Houston), senior associates Joe Cavanaugh and Alaa Salaheldin (D.C.), and associates Laura Penaranda (Los Angeles) and Devin Urness (D.C.), secured a merits victory in a series of ten bellwether
 mass arbitration proceedings alleging that Disney streaming services improperly transmitted subscribers’ personally identifying information (PII) in violation of the Video Privacy Protection Act. The team is now three-for-three on the bellwether claims, with
 this arbitrator dismissing certain Disney affiliates who were named in the dispute despite not being parties to the relevant subscriber agreements, and adopting all of the team’s remaining arguments on the merits and record evidence, which Vassi argued.&nbsp;(<b>Entertainment</b>)<o:p></o:p></span></li></ol>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:10.0pt;color:#4D5357"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>
<ol style="margin-top:0in" start="4" type="1">
<li class="MsoListParagraph" style="color:#4D5357;margin-bottom:12.0pt;margin-left:0in;mso-add-space:auto;text-align:left;line-height:normal;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1">
<a name="_Hlk174627904"><span style="font-size:10.0pt;font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif;background:white">Last week,&nbsp;senior associate Mike West, with support from senior associate Reedy Swanson, partners Cate Stetson and Jo-Ann Sagar, and appellate specialist&nbsp;Heather
 Briggs and paralegal lead&nbsp;Ashley Johnson (all D.C.), secured the release of client Bobby Ingram.&nbsp;Mike secured&nbsp;the court order reducing Bobby's life sentence to a time-served sentence through a compassionate release motion, but Mike, Reedy, and the team&nbsp;have&nbsp;been
 working to get Bobby out of jail for the past five years, through numerous filings including First Step Act motions, Eleventh Circuit appeals, and multiple cert petitions.&nbsp;<b>(Pro Bono)</b></span></a><span style="font-size:10.0pt;font-family:&quot;Calibri&quot;,sans-serif"><o:p></o:p></span></li></ol>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:10.0pt;color:#4D5357;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>
<p class="MsoNormal"><span style="font-size:10.0pt;color:#4D5357;mso-fareast-language:EN-GB">Please submit your two sentences in&nbsp;<a href="https://ehoganlovells.com/collect/click.aspx?&amp;ch=5e2f9e99006458672d51db0ecb59e43a7b5caf44" target="_blank"><span style="color:#2C5E4F">this
 online form</span></a>&nbsp;by noon each Thursday. Please reach out to&nbsp;<a href="mailto:aditya.ramachandran@hoganlovells.com"><span style="color:#2C5E4F">Adi Ramachandran</span></a>&nbsp;or&nbsp;<a href="mailto:isabeau.newnam@hoganlovells.com"><span style="color:#2C5E4F">Isa
 Newnam</span></a> if you would like your entry formatted in a way not immediately available on the form.&nbsp;<br>
<br>
We ask that each member of the practice submit proposals regularly for our&nbsp;<i>3 Things in 2 Sentences</i>&nbsp;alerts. Please submit any information on wins, significant proceedings, pro bono matters, substantial new work, articles, speaking engagements, and other
 group information.&nbsp;<br>
<br>
<br>
Thanks.<br>
<br>
- Adam<o:p></o:p></span></p>
